race.comment: OPTIMAL (1) is first-up and looks short of his best trip, though he hasn't trialled coming into this. The claim of Hayes comes in handy and the cheekers coming off is a positive sign. Can resume on a positive note. CHILEAN STAR (3) only had one run last campaign but lost no admirers as a 20-1 chance at this track and trip. Her recent trial at Lark Hill was very strong and she looks ready to run well on resumption. Can make her presence felt. NICCONAMI (5) is another who comes here off a Lark Hill trial where she was sound in her first outing for the new stable. The wide draw is a niggle, though she's open to improvement in her second racing campaign. Can feature. SOLASH MOON (8) turned in a nice trial recently and has claims despite the wide barrier. CRASHED AND BURNED (4) is next best first-up without a trial.
